The paper deals with the art gallery problem, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and complexity results, which are topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The reduction from Set Cover problem suggests connections to computational complexity (cs.CC) and the use of approximation algorithms suggests connections to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
